article.headline: Liberty 71, VMI 67
article.story: LYNCHBURG, Va. (AP) -- Evan Risher scored a jumper with less than two seconds remaining to lead Liberty to a 71-67 win over VMI on Thursday night. Larry Blair led the Flames (5-16, 2-7 Big South Conference) with 23 points and a career-high 13 rebounds. Liberty was matched point-for-point in the first half, and tied the game 31-all at halftime. Chavis Holmes scored a 3-pointer for the Keydets (7-13, 2-7), tying the game 67-all with 53 seconds left. Larry Blair then missed a 3-point shot, but Liberty rebounded and took a timeout. Risher then took the inbound pass to finish the game. VMI gave up 30 points to Liberty off of 16 turnovers. Rell Porter added 12 points and eight rebounds for the Flames, and Damien Hubbard had 10. Reggie Williams led VMI with 23 points, and Matt Murrer added 12 points and nine rebounds.
